sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client<br/>(Browser / API)
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Upstream as Upstream Application<br/>(localhost)
    participant Prom as prometheus-k8s<br/>(OpenShift Monitoring)

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client, Upstream: Flow 1: Authenticated Request Proxying
        Client->>Proxy: HTTPS Request (8443/TCP)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / x509 / OIDC JWT
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: TokenReview Response<br/>(authenticated user info)
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authorization.k8s.io/v1/subjectaccessreviews<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: SubjectAccessReview Response<br/>(allowed: true/false)
        alt Authorized
            Proxy->>Upstream: HTTP Request (localhost)<br/>+ optional auth headers
            Upstream-->>Proxy: HTTP Response
            Proxy-->>Client: HTTPS Response (TLS 1.2+)
        else Denied
            Proxy-->>Client: 403 Forbidden
        end
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over Prom, Upstream: Flow 2: Prometheus Metrics Scraping
        Prom->>Proxy: GET /metrics (8443/TCP HTTPS)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA token)
        Note over Proxy: Hardcoded authorizer bypasses SAR<br/>for system:serviceaccount:<br/>openshift-monitoring:prometheus-k8s
        Proxy->>Upstream: GET /metrics (localhost HTTP)
        Upstream-->>Proxy: Metrics Response
        Proxy-->>Prom: HTTPS Response (TLS 1.2+)
    end
